Snap Earnings
-------------

From Bloomberg ( https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-07-25/snap-fa=
lls-after-sales-forecast-misses-estimates-on-ad-demand ) :

Snap Inc. projected revenue at the lower end of analysts=E2=80=99 estimates=
 for this quarter, signaling that improvements to the digital advertising b=
usiness are taking longer than expected to pay off. The shares fell in prem=
arket trading, on course for the biggest intraday drop in three months.

This takes the stock story full circle: Microsoft might gripe that it is no=
t getting sufficient credit for long-term opportunity, while Google is rewa=
rded for showing that its core business is strong. Snap, meanwhile, is gett=
ing punished for the fact that its core business continues to be completely=
 broken.

One more bit: while Snap=E2=80=99s revenue was down 4% year-over-year, its =
cost of revenue was up 11%, which meant its gross margin fell from 59% a ye=
ar ago to 53% last quarter. I suspect that increase is due to =E2=80=9CMy A=
I=E2=80=9D, and it=E2=80=99s a bit of a cautionary tale: adding on an expen=
sive-to-provide service is a dangerous game if your business model is broke=
n.

